MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: apps/game-server/src/machines/timeline-presets\.ts$
ADVISORY: |
  Heads-up: timeline template changes do NOT backfill in-flight games.

  `sendAndCaptureGameMasterDay` (apps/game-server/src/machines/actions/
  l2-day-resolution.ts:24,87) appends a resolved day to `manifest.days[]`
  ONLY if `dayIndex` doesn't already exist:

      const alreadyExists = manifest.days.some(d => d.dayIndex === resolvedDay.dayIndex);
      if (alreadyExists) return {};

  Practical implication of any edit here:
  - Days resolved BEFORE the deploy keep their old timeline forever
  - In-flight games on day N → fix only takes effect on day N+1
  - Brand-new games created post-deploy → fix applies from day 1

  If a fix needs to apply to an in-flight game's CURRENT day:
  - Add an admin button that fires the specific event via INJECT_TIMELINE_EVENT
    (see OverviewTab.tsx "Start Confession" pattern), OR
  - Curl the admin endpoint with the event payload, OR
  - Wait for the next day transition

  Discovered 2026-04-23 while debugging "I added confession to the day
  template, why doesn't it appear in TimelineTab for this game?" Answer:
  the day's manifest was already resolved without it.
